         <abstract id="aspace_84b2dedb8f7f042240c6ee2543b5bd63">The records consist of secretaries' minutes, correspondence, subscriber lists, narrative reports of hunts, and records for Hunt-sponsored events such as the annual judging of the young hounds and the Hunt Ball, steeplechases, and Gamekeepers' and Earthstoppers' lunches and shoots. The material primarily dates from 1877, when the Linlithgow and Stirlingshire Hunt was reorganized, but also contains some records from the Lothians' Hunt period. The material was used by Hunt secretary James H. Rutherfurd for his 1911 volume The History of the Linlithgow and Stirlingshire Hunt, 1775-1910.</abstract>
